5:T4b8,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"SoftwareApplication","@id":"https://www.xrnotify.io/#app","name":"XRNotify","description":"Real-time webhook notification platform for the XRP Ledger.","url":"https://www.xrnotify.io","applicationCategory":"DeveloperApplication","operatingSystem":"Web","offers":[{"@type":"Offer","name":"Free","price":"0","priceCurrency":"USD","description":"1,000 events/month, 2 webhooks"},{"@type":"Offer","name":"Starter","price":"29.00","priceCurrency":"USD","description":"50,000 events/month, 10 webhooks, WebSocket access"},{"@type":"Offer","name":"Pro","price":"99.00","priceCurrency":"USD","description":"500,000 events/month, 50 webhooks, priority delivery"}],"creator":{"@id":"https://www.jonomor.com/ali-morgan#person"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://www.jonomor.com/#organization"},"isPartOf":{"@id":"https://www.jonomor.com/#organization"},"featureList":["Real-time XRPL event ingestion","HMAC-SHA256 signed webhook delivery","Automatic retries with exponential backoff","Dead-letter queue for failed deliveries","Event replay and reprocessing","23+ XRPL event types supported","Developer dashboard with delivery logs","Per-webhook filtering by event type and account"]}6:Tcff,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","@id":"https://www.xrnotify.io/#faqpage","name":"XRNotify FAQ — Common Questions About XRPL Webhooks","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is XRNotify?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"XRNotify is a real-time webhook notification platform for the XRP Ledger. It monitors XRPL transactions as they confirm on-chain, normalizes them into clean JSON schemas, and delivers them to your endpoints via HMAC-signed HTTPS POST requests. XRNotify eliminates the need to run your own XRPL node or build polling infrastructure."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What XRPL events does XRNotify support?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"XRNotify supports 23+ event types across all major XRPL transaction categories: payments (XRP and issued tokens), NFT operations (minting, burning, offers, transfers), DEX trades (OfferCreate, OfferCancel, AMM operations), trustline changes (TrustSet), escrow events (create, finish, cancel), check operations, and account-level changes like settings modifications and deletions."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does webhook delivery work?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"When an XRPL transaction matches your configured filters, XRNotify normalizes the event, signs the payload with your webhook secret using HMAC-SHA256, and delivers it as an HTTPS POST to your endpoint. If delivery fails, XRNotify retries with exponential backoff (up to 10 attempts over 12 hours). Events that exhaust all retries are moved to a dead-letter queue for manual inspection and replay."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is XRNotify free?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"XRNotify offers a free tier with 1,000 events per month and 2 webhook endpoints — enough for testing and hobby projects. Paid plans start at $29/month (Starter: 50,000 events, 10 webhooks, WebSocket streaming) and $99/month (Pro: 500,000 events, 50 webhooks, priority delivery). Enterprise plans with custom SLAs are available on request."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I verify webhook signatures?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Every XRNotify webhook includes an X-XRNotify-Signature header containing an HMAC-SHA256 hash of the request body, computed using your webhook signing secret. To verify, compute the HMAC-SHA256 of the raw request body with your secret and compare it to the header value using a constant-time comparison function to prevent timing attacks."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Who built XRNotify?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"XRNotify was built by Ali Morgan, founder of Jonomor, a systems architecture studio focused on AI Visibility and real-time infrastructure intelligence. XRNotify is the XRPL instrumentation layer of the Jonomor ecosystem, which also includes Guard-Clause, MyPropOps, The Neutral Bridge, Evenfield, and H.U.N.I.E."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is XRNotify part of a larger ecosystem?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. XRNotify is part of the Jonomor ecosystem, a suite of interconnected software products built by Ali Morgan. Within the ecosystem, XRNotify serves as the real-time observation layer — detecting XRPL events at the point of origin before they flow through interpretation and operational layers in other Jonomor properties."}}]}0:["pQjrRFT3j-NbWRfetFzsE",[[["",{"children":["docs",{"children":["reference",{"children":["rate-limits",{"children":["__PAGE__",{}]}]}]}]},"$undefined","$undefined",true],["",{"children":["docs",{"children":["reference",{"children":["rate-limits",{"children":["__PAGE__",{},[["$L1",["$","div",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-[#0a0a0f] text-white antialiased","children":[["$","nav",null,{"className":"border-b border-zinc-800/50","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-2 text-sm","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/docs","className":"text-zinc-500 hover:text-zinc-300 no-underline","children":"Docs"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-zinc-600","children":"/"}],["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/docs#reference","className":"text-zinc-500 hover:text-zinc-300 no-underline","children":"Reference"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-zinc-600","children":"/"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300","children":"Rate Limits"}]]}],["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/dashboard","className":"text-zinc-400 hover:text-white transition-colors text-sm no-underline","children":"Dashboard →"}]]}]}],["$","main",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"inline-block text-xs font-medium text-emerald-400 bg-emerald-500/10 border border-emerald-500/20 rounded px-2 py-0.5 mb-4","children":"Reference"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-3","children":"Rate Limits"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-400 text-lg leading-relaxed","children":"XRNotify enforces rate limits on API requests per key using a token bucket algorithm. Limits vary by plan and are designed to support high-throughput integrations on paid plans."}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Overview"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3","children":"Rate limits apply per API key, not per account. If you have multiple API keys, each operates its own independent token bucket. All API endpoints count toward the same rate limit bucket for a given key."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-emerald-500/10 border border-emerald-500/20 rounded-lg p-3 text-sm text-zinc-300","children":[["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"Webhook deliveries are not counted."}]," Inbound event deliveries from XRNotify to your endpoint do not consume API rate limit tokens. Only your outbound requests to the XRNotify API are counted."]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Limits by plan"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"overflow-x-auto","children":["$","table",null,{"className":"w-full text-sm border-collapse","children":[["$","thead",null,{"children":["$","tr",null,{"className":"border-b border-zinc-800","children":[["$","th",null,{"className":"text-left py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-400 font-medium","children":"Plan"}],["$","th",null,{"className":"text-left py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-400 font-medium","children":"Requests / minute"}],["$","th",null,{"className":"text-left py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-400 font-medium","children":"Requests / day"}],["$","th",null,{"className":"text-left py-2 text-zinc-400 font-medium","children":"Burst capacity"}]]}]}],["$","tbody",null,{"className":"divide-y divide-zinc-800/50","children":[["$","tr","Free",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6 text-zinc-300 font-medium","children":"Free"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"60"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"1,000"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 text-zinc-300","children":"20"}]]}],["$","tr","Starter",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6 text-zinc-300 font-medium","children":"Starter"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"300"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"10,000"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 text-zinc-300","children":"50"}]]}],["$","tr","Pro",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6 text-zinc-300 font-medium","children":"Pro"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"1,000"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"100,000"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 text-zinc-300","children":"200"}]]}],["$","tr","Enterprise",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6 text-zinc-300 font-medium","children":"Enterprise"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"Custom"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"Unlimited"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 text-zinc-300","children":"Custom"}]]}]]}]]}]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Token bucket algorithm"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["XRNotify uses a token bucket algorithm for rate limiting. Each API key starts with a bucket of tokens equal to its plan's burst capacity. Every API request consumes one token from the bucket. The bucket refills continuously at a rate of"," ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 bg-zinc-800 px-1 rounded","children":"(requests_per_minute / 60)"}]," tokens per second, up to the burst capacity ceiling."]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"For example, a Pro plan key refills at roughly 16.7 tokens/second and can absorb a burst of 200 requests before the rate limit is enforced. This means short bursts of activity are handled gracefully without triggering 429 errors, as long as the average request rate over time stays within the per-minute limit."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4","children":["$","pre",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm font-mono whitespace-pre","children":"# Token bucket refill rate formula:\nrefill_rate = requests_per_minute / 60   # tokens per second\n\n# Example for Pro plan:\nrefill_rate = 1000 / 60 = ~16.7 tokens/second\nburst_capacity = 200 tokens\n\n# A burst of 200 requests is absorbed instantly.\n# After the burst, the bucket refills at 16.7/s.\n# Sustained rate above 1000 req/min will trigger 429."}]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Rate limit headers"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"Every API response includes the following headers so you can monitor your usage and slow down proactively before hitting the limit:"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"overflow-x-auto mb-4","children":["$","table",null,{"className":"w-full text-sm border-collapse","children":[["$","thead",null,{"children":["$","tr",null,{"className":"border-b border-zinc-800","children":[["$","th",null,{"className":"text-left py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-400 font-medium","children":"Header"}],["$","th",null,{"className":"text-left py-2 text-zinc-400 font-medium","children":"Description"}]]}]}],["$","tbody",null,{"className":"divide-y divide-zinc-800/50","children":[["$","tr","X-RateLimit-Limit",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 text-xs whitespace-nowrap","children":"X-RateLimit-Limit"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 text-zinc-300 text-xs leading-relaxed","children":"Your plan's requests per minute limit."}]]}],["$","tr","X-RateLimit-Remaining",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 text-xs whitespace-nowrap","children":"X-RateLimit-Remaining"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 text-zinc-300 text-xs leading-relaxed","children":"Number of tokens remaining in the current bucket."}]]}],["$","tr","X-RateLimit-Reset",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 text-xs whitespace-nowrap","children":"X-RateLimit-Reset"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 text-zinc-300 text-xs leading-relaxed","children":"Unix timestamp when the bucket will be full again."}]]}],["$","tr","Retry-After",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 pr-6","children":["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 text-xs whitespace-nowrap","children":"Retry-After"}]}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2.5 text-zinc-300 text-xs leading-relaxed","children":"Seconds to wait before retrying. Only present on 429 responses."}]]}]]}]]}]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Handling 429 responses"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":["When you receive a 429 response, read the"," ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 bg-zinc-800 px-1 rounded","children":"Retry-After"}]," header and wait that many seconds before retrying. The following example implements a simple retry helper with respect for the server-provided delay:"]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4","children":["$","pre",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm font-mono whitespace-pre","children":"async function apiCall(url, options, retries = 3) {\n  const response = await fetch(url, options);\n\n  if (response.status === 429 && retries > 0) {\n    const retryAfter = parseInt(response.headers.get('Retry-After') || '5', 10);\n    console.warn(`Rate limited. Waiting ${retryAfter}s before retry...`);\n    await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, retryAfter * 1000));\n    return apiCall(url, options, retries - 1);\n  }\n\n  if (!response.ok) {\n    const error = await response.json();\n    throw new Error(`API error: ${error.error.code} — ${error.error.message}`);\n  }\n\n  return response.json();\n}\n\n// Usage:\nconst webhooks = await apiCall('https://api.xrnotify.io/v1/webhooks', {\n  headers: { 'X-XRNotify-Key': process.env.XRNOTIFY_API_KEY },\n});"}]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Exponential backoff for persistent 429s"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"If you're consistently hitting the rate limit, use exponential backoff with jitter to spread retries over time and avoid a retry thundering herd:"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4","children":["$","pre",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm font-mono whitespace-pre","children":"async function apiCallWithBackoff(url, options, attempt = 0) {\n  const MAX_ATTEMPTS = 5;\n  const response = await fetch(url, options);\n\n  if (response.status === 429 && attempt < MAX_ATTEMPTS) {\n    // Use server's Retry-After if available, otherwise exponential backoff\n    const serverDelay = parseInt(response.headers.get('Retry-After') || '0', 10);\n    const exponential = Math.pow(2, attempt) * 1000; // 1s, 2s, 4s, 8s, 16s\n    const jitter = Math.random() * 500;              // up to 500ms jitter\n    const delay = Math.max(serverDelay * 1000, exponential + jitter);\n\n    await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, delay));\n    return apiCallWithBackoff(url, options, attempt + 1);\n  }\n\n  return response;\n}"}]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Best practices"}],["$","ul",null,{"className":"space-y-3 text-zinc-300 text-sm","children":[["$","li",null,{"className":"flex gap-3","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5","children":"→"}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"Cache GET responses."}]," Webhook lists, delivery logs, and stats do not change on every request. Cache them for 30–60 seconds to dramatically reduce API call volume."]}]]}],["$","li",null,{"className":"flex gap-3","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5","children":"→"}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"Batch operations."}]," When creating multiple webhooks or retrying multiple deliveries, stagger your requests rather than firing them all simultaneously. A short sleep between requests protects your burst budget."]}]]}],["$","li",null,{"className":"flex gap-3","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5","children":"→"}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"Monitor X-RateLimit-Remaining."}]," When the remaining token count drops below 20% of your limit, slow your request rate proactively — before you hit 0 and start receiving 429 errors."]}]]}],["$","li",null,{"className":"flex gap-3","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5","children":"→"}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"Use the Retry-After header."}]," Always respect the server-provided delay. Using a fixed backoff shorter than the server's window will result in wasted requests that still fail."]}]]}],["$","li",null,{"className":"flex gap-3","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5","children":"→"}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"Consider upgrading your plan."}]," If you consistently need more than 60 requests/minute, the Starter or Pro plan may be more appropriate. Contact us for Enterprise limits."]}]]}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Next steps"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3","children":[["$","$L2","/docs/reference/error-codes",{"href":"/docs/reference/error-codes","className":"block bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 hover:border-zinc-700 transition-colors no-underline","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"text-sm font-medium text-white mb-1","children":"Error Codes"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"text-xs text-zinc-500","children":"Full error code reference including 429 format"}]]}],["$","$L2","/docs/reference/retry-policy",{"href":"/docs/reference/retry-policy","className":"block bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 hover:border-zinc-700 transition-colors no-underline","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"text-sm font-medium text-white mb-1","children":"Retry Policy"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"text-xs text-zinc-500","children":"How XRNotify retries failed webhook deliveries"}]]}],["$","$L2","/docs/api/webhooks",{"href":"/docs/api/webhooks","className":"block bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 hover:border-zinc-700 transition-colors no-underline","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"text-sm font-medium text-white mb-1","children":"Webhooks API"}],["$","div",null,{"cla